obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42224)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42224&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Provident Funds`
  line `Act, 1925.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1`
  line `[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*] ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1851, s. 3 and Schedule, for "except Part B States".`
  line
  line `2. The words "including British Baluchistan" omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line
  line `3. 1st April, 1926, Gazette of India, 1925, Pt. I, p. 1182.`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42225)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42225&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `(a) "compulsory deposit" means a subscription to, or deposit in, a Provident Fund which,`
  line `under the rules of the Fund, is not, until the happening of some specified contingency,`
  line `repayable on demand otherwise than for the purpose of the payment of, premia in respect of a`
  line `policy of life insurance, ^1[or the payment of subscriptions or premia in respect of a family`
  line `pension fund], and includes any contribution ^2*** and any interest or increment which has`
  line `accrued under the rules of the fund on any such subscription, deposit or contribution, and`
  line `also any such subscription, deposit, contribution, interest or increment remaining to the credit`
  line `of the subscriber or depositor after the happening of any such contingency;`
  line
  line `(b) "contribution" means any amount credited in a Provident Fund, by ^3[any authority`
  line `administering the Fund], by way of addition to, ^4[a subscription to, or deposit or balance`
  line `at the credit of an individual account in,] the Fund; and contributory Provident Fund`
  line `means a Provident Fund the rules of which provide for the crediting of contributions;`
  line
  line `(c) "dependant" means any of the following relatives of -`
  line `a deceased subscriber to, or a`
  line `depositor in, a Provident Fund, namely, a wife, husband, parent, child, minor brother,`
  line `unmarried sister and a deceased son's widow and child, and, where no parent of the`
  line `subscriber or depositor is alive, a paternal grand-parent;`
  line
  line `(d) "Government Provident Fund means a Provident Fund, other than a`
  line `Railway Provident Fund, constituted by the authority of ^5`
  line `the Secretary of State, the`
  line `Central Government, the Crown Representative or any State Government] for any class or`
  line `classes of ^6[persons in the service of the Government] or ^7[of persons employed in`
  line `educational institutions or employed by bodies existing solely for educational purposes,]^8`
  line `and references in this Act to the Government shall be construed accordingly;]`
  line
  line `(e) "Provident Fund" means a fund in which subscriptions or deposits of any class or`
  line `classes of employees are received and held on their individual accounts, and includes any`
  line `contributions ^9*** and any interest or increment accruing on such subscriptions, deposits or`
  line `contributions under the rules of the Fund;`
  line
  line `^10[(f) "Railway administration" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any company administering a railway or tramway in ^11`
  line `any part of India] either`
  line `under a special Act of Parliament ^12`
  line `[of the United Kingdom] or an Indian law, or`
  line `under contract with the Government, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the manager of any railway or tramway administered by the Central Government] or by a`
  line `State Government,`
  line
  line `and includes, in any case referred to in sub-clause (ii) the ^13[Central Government] or the. State`
  line `Government, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(g) "Railway Provident Fund" means a Provident Fund constituted by the authority of a rail`
  line `Way administration for any class or classes of its employees.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1930, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. The words "credited in respect of any such subscription or deposit" omitted by s. 2, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 1925, s. 2, for "the authority by which the Fund has been constituted".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 1 of 1930, s. 2, for "or otherwise in respect of, a subscription to, or deposit in",.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Government".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 1942, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "its employees".`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 7 of 1927, s. 2, for "for teachers in educational institutions".`
  line `8. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `9. The words "credited in respect of such subscriptions or deposits" omitted by Act 1 of 1930, s.2.`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for clause (f).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "a part A State or a part C State".`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Federal Railway Authority".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42226)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Protection of compulsory deposits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42226&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) A compulsory deposit in any Government or`
  line `Railway Provident Fund shall not in any way be capable of being assigned or charged and shall`
  line `not be liable to attachment under any decree or order of any Civil, Revenue or Criminal Court in`
  line `respect of any debt or liability incurred by the subscriber or depositor, and neither the Official`
  line `Assignee nor any receiver appointed under the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920),`
  line `shall be entitled to, or have any claim on, any such compulsory deposit.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sum standing to the credit of any subscriber to, or depositor in, any such Fund at`
  line `the time of his decease and payable under the rules of the Fund to any dependant of the`
  line `subscriber or depositor, or to such person as may be authorised by law to receive payment o n`
  line `his behalf, shall, subject to any deduction authorised by this Act and, save where the`
  line `dependant is the widow or child of the subscriber or depositor, subject also to the rights of an`
  line `assignee under an assignment made before the commencement of this Act, vest in the`
  line `dependant, and shall, subject as aforesaid, be free from any debt or other liability incurred by`
  line `the deceased or incurred by the dependant before the death of the subscriber or depositor .`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42227)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Provisions regarding re-payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42227&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) When under the rules of any Government or`
  line `Railway Provident Fund the sum standing to the credit of any subscriber or depositor, or the`
  line `balance thereof after the making of any deduction authorised by this Act, has become payable,`
  line `the officer whose duty is to make the payment shall pay the sum or balance, as the case may`
  line `be, to the subscriber or depositor, or, if he is dead, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) if the sum or balance, or, any part thereof, vests in a dependant under the`
  line `provisions of section 3, pay the same to the dependant or to such person as may be`
  line `authorised by law to receive payment on his behalf; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the whole sum or balance, as the case may be, does not exceed five thousand`
  line `rupees, pay the same, or any part thereof, which is not payable under clause ( a), to any`
  line `person nominated to receive it under the rules of the Fund, or, if no person is so nominated,`
  line `to any person appearing to him to be otherwise entitled to receive it; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of any sum or balance, or any part thereof, which is not payable to any person`
  line `under clause (a) or clause (b) pay the same,--`
  line
  line `(i) to any person nominated to receive it under the rules of the Fund, on production`
  line `by such person of probate or letters of administration evidencing the grant to him of`
  line `administration to the estate of the deceased or a certificate granted under the Succession`
  line `Certificate Act, 1889 ^1(7 of 1889), or under the Bombay Regulation VIII of 1827,`
  line `entitling the holder thereof to receive payment of such sum, balance or part, or`
  line
  line `(ii) where no person is so nominated, to any person who produces such probate, letters`
  line `or certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the whole or any part of any sum standing to the credit of the`
  line `subscriber or depositor has been assigned to any other person before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, and notice in writing of the assignment has been received by t he officer from the assignee,`
  line `the officer shall, after making any deduction authorised by this Act and any payment due under`
  line `clause (a) to or on behalf of the widow or children of the subscriber or depositor--`
  line
  line `(i) if the subscriber or depositor or, if he is dead, the person to whom in the absence`
  line `of any valid assignment the sum or balance would be payable under this sub -section`
  line `gives his consent in writing, pay the sum or part or the balance thereof, as the case may`
  line `be, to the assignee, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if such consent is not forthcoming, withhold payment of the sum, part or balance, as the`
  line `case may be, pending a decision of a competent Civil Court as to the person entitled to receive it.`
  line
  line `(2) The making of any payment authorised by sub-section (1) shall be a full discharge to the`
  line `Government or the railway administration, as the case may be, from all liability in respect of so`
  line `much of the sum standing to the credit of the subscriber or depositor as is equivalent to the`
  line `amount so paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42228)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Rights of nominees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42228&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time`
  line `being in force or in any disposition, whether testamentary or otherwise, by a subscriber to, or`
  line `depositor in, a Government or Railway Provident Fund of the sum standing to his credit in the`
  line `Fund, or of any part thereof, where any nomination, duly made in accordance with the rules of`
  line `the Fund, purports to confer upon any person the right to receive the whole or any part of such`
  line `sum on the death of the subscriber or depositor occurring before the sum has become payable or`
  line `before the sum, having become payable, has been paid, the said person shall, on the death as`
  line `aforesaid of the subscriber or depositor, become entitled, to the exclusion of all other persons, to`
  line `receive such sum or part thereof, as the case may be, unless--`
  line
  line `(a) such nomination is at any time varied by another nomination made in like manner or`
  line `expressly cancelled by notice given in the manner and to the authority prescribed by those`
  line `rules, or`
  line
  line `(b) such nomination at any time becomes invalid by reason of the happening of some`
  line `contingency specified therein,--`
  line
  line `and if the said person predeceases the subscriber or depositor, the nomination shall, so far as it`
  line `relates to the right conferred upon the said person, become void and of no effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that where provision has been duly made in the nomination in accordance with`
  line `the rules of the Fund, conferring upon some other person such right in the stead of the person deceased, such right shall, upon the decease as aforesaid of the said pers on, pass to such other`
  line person.]
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in ^2[the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925)]`
  line `or the Bombay Regulation VIII of 1827, any ^3[person, who becomes entitled as aforesaid, may`
  line `be granted] a certificate-under that Act, or that Regulation, as the case may be, entitling him to`
  line `receive payment of such sum or part, and such certificate shall not be deemed to be invalidated`
  line `or superseded by any grant to any other person of probate or letters of administration to the`
  line `estate of the deceased.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The provisions of this section as amended by sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Provident Funds`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1946 (11 of 1946), shall apply also to all such nominations made before the date of`
  line `the commencement of that Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this section as so amended shall not operate to affect any`
  line `case, in which before the said date any sum has been paid, or has under the rules of the Fu nd`
  line `become payable in pursuance of any nomination duly made in accordance with those rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1946, s. 2, for sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 35 of 1950, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "the Succession Certificate Act, 1889".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1946, s. 2, for certain words.`
  line
  line `4. Added by s. 2, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42229)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to make deductions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42229&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `When the sum standing to the credit of any subscriber or`
  line `depositor in any Government or Railway Provident Fund which is a contributory Provident`
  line `Fund becomes payable, there may, if the authority ^1[specified in this behalf in. the rules of the`
  line `fund] so directs, be deducted therefrom and paid to ^2[Government or the Railway administation, as the case may bed],--`
  line
  line `(a) any amount due under a liability incurred by the subscriber or depositor to`
  line `^2[Government or the Railway administration], but not exceeding in any case the total`
  line `amount of any contributions credited to the account of the subscriber or depositor and of`
  line `any interest or increment which has accrued on such contributions; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the subscriber or depositor has been dismissed from ^3[his employment]`
  line `for any reasons specified in this behalf in the rules of the Fund, or where he has`
  line `resigned such employment within five years of the commencement thereof, the whole`
  line `or any part of the amount of any such contributions, interest and increment.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 1925, s. 3, for "by which the Fund has been constituted".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "that authority".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "the employment of that authority".`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (42230)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Withholding or recovery of Government contributions in case of Central Government officers taking up, without prior permission, commercial employment within two years of their retirement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1975, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42230&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Withholding or recovery of Government contributions in case of Central`
  line `Government officers taking up, without prior permission, commercial employment within`
  line `two years of their retirement.--(1) In this section, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Central Government officer" means a subscriber to, or depositor in, a contributory`
  line `provident fund constituted by the Central Government, who, immediately before his`
  line `retirement, is a member of a Central Service Class I, but does not include an officer`
  line `appointed under a contract of service for a specified term;`
  line
  line `(b) "commercial employment" means employment in any capacity (including that of`
  line `an agent) under any company, co-operative society, firm or individual engaged in`
  line `trading, commercial, industrial, financial or professional business and includes also--`
  line
  line `(i) a directorship of a company;`
  line
  line `(ii) the holding of any office, whether elective or otherwise, such as that of`
  line `president, chairman, manager, secretary, treasurer, by whatever name called in a co -`
  line `operative society; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the setting up of practice, either independently or as partner of a firm, as`
  line `adviser or consultant in matters in respect of which the Central Government officer,--`
  line
  line `(A) has no prefessional qualifications and the matters in respect of which`
  line `the practice is to be set up or is carried on are relatable to his official knowledge or`
  line `experience, or`
  line
  line `(B) has professional qualification, but the matters in respect of which such practice is to`
  line `be set up are such as are likely to give his clients an unfair advantage by reason of the posts`
  line `held by him under the Central Government, or`
  line
  line `(C) has to undertake work involving liaison or contact with the offices or officers of`
  line `Central Government,`
  line
  line `but does not include employment in or under a corporation or company wholly or substantially`
  line `owned or controlled by Government or employment in or under a body controlled_ or financed`
  line `wholly or substantially by Government;`
  line
  line `(c) "Government contributions" means contributions made after the commencement of the`
  line `Provident Funds (Amendment) Act, 1975 (46 of 1975), in respect of any period after such`
  line `commencement, by the Central Government or by a State Government or by a local authority within`
  line `the meaning of the Local Authorities Loans Act, 1914 (9 of 1914);`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) No Central Government officer shall have any right to the Government contributions made to his`
  line `credit in a contributory provident fund in any case where he takes up commercial employment at any`
  line `time before the expiry of two years from the date of his retirement without the prior permission of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this sub-section and sub-section (7), "date of retirement" in`
  line `relation to a Central Government officer re-employed after retirement without any break either in the`
  line `same or any other Class I post under the Central Government or any other equivalent post under a State`
  line `Government, shall mean the date on which such Central Government officer finally ceases to be reemployed in Government service.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--A Central Government officer permitted by the Central Government to take up a`
  line `particular commercial employment during his leave preparatory to retirement shall be deemed, for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-section, to have obtained prior permission of the Central Government for his`
  line `continuance in such employment after retirement.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the Central Government may, by order in`
  line `writing, on an application made in the prescribed form by a Central Government officer, grant,`
  line `subject to such conditions, if any, as it may deem necessary, permission, or refuse, for rea sons to`
  line `be recorded in the order, permission, to such officer to take up the commercial employment`
  line `specified in the application.`
  line
  line `(4) In granting or refusing permission under this section to a Central Government officer for`
  line `taking up any commercial employment, the Central Government shall have regard to the following`
  line `factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of the employment proposed to be taken up and the antecedents of the`
  line employer;
  line
  line `(b) whether his duties in the employment which he proposes to take up might be such as to bring`
  line `him into conflict with Government;`
  line
  line `(c) whether the officer while in service had any such dealing with the employer under whom lie`
  line `proposes to seek employment as might afford a reasonable basis for the suspicion that such officer`
  line `had shown favours to such employer;`
  line
  line `(d) any other relevant factors which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Where within a period of sixty days of the date of receipt of an application under`
  line `sub-section (3), the Central Government does not refuse to grant the permission applied for`
  line `or does not communicate the refusal to the applicant, the Central Government shall be deemed to have`
  line `granted the permission applied for.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Central Government grants the permission applied for subject to any`
  line `conditions or refuses such permission, the applicant may, within thirty days of the receipt of`
  line `the order of the Central Government to that effect, make a representation against any such`
  line `condition or refusal and the Central Government may make such orders thereon as it deems`
  line `fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order other than an order cancelling such condition or granting such`
  line `permission without any conditions shall be made under this sub -section without giving the`
  line `person making the representation an opportunity to show cause against the order proposed to`
  line `be made.`
  line
  line `(7) if any Central Government officer takes up any commercial employment at any time`
  line `before the expiry of two years from the date of his retirement without the prior permission of`
  line `the Central Government or commits a breach of any condition Subject to which permission to`
  line `take up any commercial employment has been granted to him under this section, it shall be`
  line `competent for the Central Government to declare by order in writing and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded therein that he shall not be entitled to such part of the Government contributions made`
  line `in relation to such officer as may be specified in the order and if he has received payment`
  line `thereof, to direct that he shall refund to the Central Government an amount equivalent to such`
  line `part of the Government contributions:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made without giving the officer concerned an opportunity of`
  line `showing cause against such declaration or direction:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in making any order under this sub-section, the Central Government shall have`
  line `regard to the following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the financial circumstances of the officer concerned;`
  line
  line `(ii). the nature of, and the emoluments from, the commercial employment taken up by the`
  line `officer concerned;`
  line
  line `(iii) such other relevant factors as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) Any amount required to be refunded by an order under sub -section (7) may, if it is`
  line `not refunded within the prescribed period, be recovered as arrears of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(9) Every order passed by the Central Government under this section shall be communicated to the`
  line `officer concerned.`
  line
  line `(10) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in any other provision of this Act or the rules applicable to any contributory`
  line `provident fund.`
  line
  line `(11) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and`
  line `if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions`
  line `aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that`
  line `the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall`
  line `be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42231)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Protection for acts done in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42231&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42232)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to apply the Act to other Provident Funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668&sectionId=42232&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00042_1925_1523349607668
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The ^2[appropriate Government] may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the provisions of this Act ^3[(except section 6A)] shall`
  line `apply to any Provident Fund established for the benefit of its employees by any local authority`
  line `within the meaning of the Local Authorities Loans Act, 1914 (9 of 1914), and, on the making of`
  line `such declaration, this Act shall apply accordingly, as if such Provident Fund were a Government`
  line `Provident Fund and such local authority were the Government.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) The ^5[appropriate Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that`
  line `the provisions of this Act ^6[(except section 6A)] shall apply to any Provident Fund established for`
  line `the benefit of the employees of any of the institutions specified in the Schedule, or of any group of`
  line `such institutions, and, on the making of such declaration, this Act shall apply accordingly, as if`
  line `such Provident Fund were a Government Provident Fund and the authority having custody of the`
  line `Fund were the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that section 6 shall apply as if the authority making the contributions referred to in that`
  line `section were the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^5[appropriate Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, add to the Schedule`
  line `the name of any public institution it may deem fit, and any such addition shall take effect as if it had`
  line `been made by this Act.]`
  line
  line `^7[(4) In this section "the appropriate Government" means--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to a cantonment authority, a port authority for a major port, and any`
  line `institution which, or the objects of which, appear to the Central Government to fall within`
  line `List I in the Seventh Schedule to ^8[the Constitution], the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in other cases, the State Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"The State Government" in relation to an institution registered under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) means the State Government of the State in which the`
  line `society is registered.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 8 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 1 of 1930, s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 46 of 1975, s. 3 (w.e.f. 7-2-1977).`
  line
  line `4. Added by Act 1 of 1930, s. 3.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "G.G. in C.".`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 46 of 1975, s. 3 (w.e.f. 7-2-1977).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the Government of India Act, 1935".`
